---
title: How Omni provisions the Wi-Fi Proxmox GPU worker
config:
  layout: elk
---
flowchart LR
  accTitle: Wi-Fi Proxmox Talos GPU worker architecture
  accDescr: Git and Omni define a Talos worker request. A Proxmox provider on the management NUC creates a VM on the Dell host, attaches the mapped GTX 1050 Ti, and the worker joins the existing cluster through the ASUS media bridge.

  subgraph MANAGEMENT["MANAGEMENT"]
    direction LR
    GIT["`Git desired state
    machine class + template`"]
    OMNI["`Omni
    machine lifecycle`"]
    PROVIDER["`Proxmox provider
    one Dell API endpoint`"]
    GIT desired@--> OMNI
    OMNI request@--> PROVIDER
  end

  subgraph WIFI["WI-FI SITE"]
    direction LR
    BRIDGE["`ASUS media bridge
    Ethernet over Wi-Fi`"]
    PVE["`Dell Proxmox
    VFIO + PCI mapping`"]
    VM["`Talos worker VM
    static address + GTX 1050 Ti`"]
    BRIDGE link@<--> PVE
    PVE create@--> VM
  end

  subgraph CLUSTER["KUBERNETES"]
    direction TB
    CORE["`Existing wired core
    control plane + RTX 3090 worker`"]
    VXLAN["`Cilium VXLAN
    node-IP transport`"]
    CORE corePath@--> VXLAN
    VM dellPath@--> VXLAN
  end

  PROVIDER provision@--> PVE

  classDef action fill:#fde8e8,stroke:#dc8c8c,color:#17212b
  classDef desired fill:#e1f3e8,stroke:#7bc397,color:#17212b
  classDef controller fill:#dff4f6,stroke:#70bcc4,color:#17212b
  classDef external fill:#fff3df,stroke:#d8ad55,color:#17212b
  class GIT desired
  class OMNI,PROVIDER,PVE,VM controller
  class BRIDGE external
  class CORE,VXLAN action

  desired@{ animation: slow }
  request@{ animation: fast }
  provision@{ animation: fast }
  link@{ animation: fast }
  create@{ animation: fast }
  corePath@{ animation: slow }
  dellPath@{ animation: slow }
